# Chapter 1 writing standards

## Scope

Applies only to `latex/content/chapters/chapter1.tex`.

## Chapter heading behavior

- Use a single `\chapter{บทนำ}`; do not create fake chapter titles with manual formatting.
- Keep chapter labels stable for cross-references.
- Do not manually type chapter numbering in body text when LaTeX already manages it.

## Numbering and references

- Let LaTeX manage section/figure/table/equation numbers.
- Do not hard-code figure numbers in prose; use `\ref`.
- Use unique labels for all major figures and tables.

## Style

- Use formal academic Thai.
- Keep technical English terms where clearer (e.g. BLE beacon, RSSI fingerprinting, KNN, MCP).
- Keep enumerate spacing compact and consistent with existing local Chapter 1 settings.

## Project constraints

- Do not insert template sample chapters into thesis body.
- Keep Chapter 1 figure files under `latex/assets/figures/chapter1/` to match existing `\IfFileExists` paths.
