# Chapter 1 — writing standards (TU manual alignment)

## Scope

Applies when editing [`latex/content/chapters/chapter1.tex`](latex/content/chapters/chapter1.tex). Coordinate with the project-wide thesis rule; this file is **Chapter 1–only** detail.

## Chapter heading behavior

- Use a single `\chapter{บทนำ}` as the chapter title. Do **not** fake a chapter heading with manual bold/large text or duplicate titles.
- Keep `\label{chapter1}` (or the project’s agreed intro label) stable for cross-references; avoid renaming labels without updating all `\ref`/`\autoref` targets.
- Do not prepend manual “บทที่ 1” text in the body unless the class/manual explicitly requires it in prose; chapter numbering comes from the document class.

## Numbering discipline

- Rely on LaTeX for **section**, **figure**, **table**, and **equation** numbering. Do **not** hard-code numbers (e.g. “รูปที่ 1.3”) in running text unless the manual requires a one-off exception—prefer `\ref{fig:...}` / `\autoref`.
- Keep `\section{...}` hierarchy consistent: no skipped levels, no orphan headings.
- Figures/tables: one `\caption` per float; `\label` after `\caption`; unique, stable prefixes (`fig:ch1_...`, `tab:ch1_...`).

## Formal Thai academic style

- Use **formal academic Thai**; avoid colloquialisms, excessive abbreviations in prose, and promotional tone.
- **Technical English** is allowed where standard in the field (e.g. BLE beacon, RSSI fingerprinting, KNN, MCP); do not invent awkward Thai replacements for established terms.
- **Numbered lists** (`enumerate`): avoid extra vertical space between items; in this chapter use the local `\begingroup` + `\setlist[enumerate]{...}` pattern so list spacing matches TU-style dense lists without breaking paragraph spacing elsewhere.

## Template / example chapter

- Do **not** paste or `\include` the template **example** chapter into the thesis main file or into Chapter 1. Cookbook/demo content stays outside the submission PDF (see project README / `latex/doc/`).
- New material should read as continuous thesis prose, not leftover template boilerplate.

## Assets

- Chapter 1 figures: PDFs under `latex/assets/figures/chapter1/` with names matching `\IfFileExists` stubs in `chapter1.tex` (e.g. `ch1-fig01-accessibility.pdf`).
